                                    {
                                        "type": "text",
                                        "text": "For the language designer, learning the Language Esperanto fluently imo offers an intuitive feel/exploration tool for human grammar that not much else will"
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "rich_text_section",
                                "elements": [
                                    {
                                        "type": "text",
                                        "text": "All of "
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "type": "link",
                                        "url": "https://github.com/matthiasn/talk-transcripts",
                                        "text": "Rich Hickeys talks/transcripts"
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "type": "text",
                                        "text": " will reduce fear of transforming deep philosophy into practical language design"
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "rich_text_section",
                                "elements": [
                                    {
                                        "type": "link",
                                        "url": "https://www.amazon.com/Constructing-User-Interface-Statecharts-Horrocks/dp/0201342782",
                                        "text": "Constructing the User Interface with Statecharts"
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "type": "text",
                                        "text": " (yes, there is a free pdf somewhere on the web!) this is a mind-opener in a very practical sense"
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "rich_text_section",
                                "elements": [
                                    {
                                        "type": "text",
                                        "text": "David Harel\u2019s original statechart paper and especially his paper "
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "type": "link",
                                        "url": "https://www.wisdom.weizmann.ac.il/~harel/SCANNED.PAPERS/VisualFormalisms.pdf",
                                        "text": "On Visual Formalisms"
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "type": "text",
                                        "text": " (avoid all papers about how to merge statecharts with OO, as that added some tooling for handling complexity in OO, but detracted from imo more fruitful directions such as generalizing (like letting them mingle with ADT\u2019s "
